From f47e56135fb1a2a47865c3f40243b0d9f62f3bb8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Julia Zhang <julia.zhang@amd.com>
Date: Mon, 25 Sep 2023 22:45:54 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] vrend: support linear gbm_bo blob resources for dGPU prime

Add support for creating gbm_bo backed blob resources that can be shared
between iGPU and a passthrough dGPU in the guest. With this, guest could
blit dGPU rendered data to host linear resource directly.

The resource is created in two phases:
1. PIPE_RESOURCE_CREATE allocates a large enough gbm_bo
2. PIPE_RESOURCE_SET_TYPE imports it into GL via mem_obj according to
   the gbm_bo fd

So the key change is to allow linear targets to keep gbm_bo and create a
GL texture backed by gbm_bo and let guest map the blob resource so that
guest/host can share this resource directly to support dGPU prime.

Signed-off-by: Julia Zhang <julia.zhang@amd.com>
---
 src/virglrenderer.c        |   6 +-
 src/virglrenderer.h        |   1 +
 src/vrend/vrend_renderer.c | 120 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++---------
 src/vrend/vrend_renderer.h |   2 +-
 4 files changed, 96 insertions(+), 33 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/virglrenderer.c b/src/virglrenderer.c
index 79717fcc6..925b4dae4 100644
